<TITLE> Ex-state minister's son faces arrest warrant </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 29 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Monday ordered arrest of former BNP state minister Ziaul Huq Zia's son Mashfiqul Huq in a tax-dodge case. Judge Azizul Huq issued a warrant of arrest after deputy tax commissioner of the National Board of Revenue Mamtaz Uddin lodged a case with the Senior Special Judge's Court, Dhaka. The court recorded Mamtaz's statement. According to case details, Mashfiqul dodged Tk 90.43 lakh in tax payment during 2002-03 to 2006-07 tax years. He has been charged with not disclosing while filing his income tax returns that he had Tk 3.62 crore in assets earned in the same period. bdnew
